Variables
simConfig
var simConfig

This variable stores the most valueable data for the simulation, as it contains the currently active parameters for the:

  • patient pathology and parameters,

  • simulated measurements and corresponding shown measurement parameters,

  • defibrilator pathology (to change to after a shock),

  • synchonized timer, etc.

oldConfig
var oldConfig

This variable stores the previous simConfig in order to enable dynamic changes of parameters from old to new values.

tempConfig
var tempConfig

This variable is used to store a deepcopy of the current simConfig so that temporary changes are not direcly effecting the simConfig. This is used before the shock is applied for the defibrilation. (Remember: Call by Reference is standard for Objects in JS)

defaultPathologyList
var defaultPathologyList

This variable stores a list of Pathologies, which are predefied for every new patient.

chargeValue
var chargeValue

This variable stores the currently chosen charge Value.

peakSoundVolume
var peakSoundVolume

This variable stores the currently active ECG or SpO2 Peak Volume.

shouldUseScaling
var shouldUseScaling

This variable defines, if the Vital-Signs-Graphs should s cale automatically. IS CURRENTLY NOT IN USE!

screenVisible
var screenVisible

This variable defines if the simulated monitor is on or off.

isRangeSliderInitilized
var isRangeSliderInitilized

This variable is a flag that stores, if the Range Sliders where already initialized.

nibpOneSecondTimer
var nibpOneSecondTimer

This variable stores the one second interval Timer for the decrease of the nibpIntervalDuration.

nibpCountdownInterval
var nibpCountdownInterval

This variable stores the currently chosen NIBP-Interval.

nibpIntervalDuration
var nibpIntervalDuration

This variable contains the duration of the NIBP-Interval. Ranging from 60sec to 5*60sec.

changeDuration
var changeDuration

This variable contains the DataModel for the changeDuration.

graphsPaused
var graphsPaused

Indicates, if the Graphs are paused. Used for UI-states.

etco2Calculation
var etco2Calculation

Used to perform all calculations to simulate the etco2-curve.

ecgCalculation
var ecgCalculation

Used to perform all calculations to simulate the ecg-curve.

spo2Calculation
var spo2Calculation

Used to perform all calculations to simulate the spo2-curve.

Functions
initControls
var initControls = function (
newConfig
)

Called every second and when the values in the UI-Elements change. Responsible for initializing the UI and for setting the current config.

Parameters
newConfig

Contains the current or new config. It is set to simConfig.

screenOnOff
function screenOnOff()

This function turns the simulated display screen on and off.

initIonRangeSlider
function initIonRangeSlider()

This function initializes the Range Slider that are shown in the Settings-Modal.  It is called by getAlarmLevels and only executed once at the beginning.

togglePauseGraphs
function togglePauseGraphs()

This function is used to toggle the Pause-Mode for the three Graphs.

takeScreenshot
function takeScreenshot()

This function is used to take a Screenshot from the current Traineeview.  The screenshot is then stored in a folder on the serverside.

See also: This functionality is provided by html2canvas

formatTime
function formatTime(
seconds
)

This function turns a number into a correcly formatted h:mm:ss format.

Parameters
seconds

contains the value of the time that should be formatted (in seconds).

getNIBP
function getNIBP(
interval = -1
)

This function will either start a one-time or repeated NIBP-Measurement. If an Interval is defined, the nibpIntervalDuration and nibpCountdownInterval are defined and the nibpOneSecondTimer is started. Additionally, the Icon is toggled and the Modal closed.

Parameters
interval

Defines the Interval for the NIBP. (Contains values from 1 to 5 if specified.) Default value is -1 which indicated that no interval is chosen and a singletime NIBP is requested.

nibpRepetitionTimer
function nibpRepetitionTimer()

When called, this function decreases the nibpIntervalDuration by 1 and eventually stops the nibpOneSecondTimer if nibpIntervalDuration is 0. Then, the NIBP Measurement (Soundfile) is restarted again. The function also updates the Label for the NIBP-Countdown using th function formatTime.

See Also: getNIBP

stopNIBPInterval
function stopNIBPInterval()

When called, this function stops clears the nibpOneSecondTimer timer and resets the corresponding UI-Elements.

addNIBPHistory
function addNIBPHistory(
nibpValue
)

This function is used to add the latest measurement value to the NIBP History.

Parameters
nibpValue

Contains most recent the NIBP Value.

getAlarmLevels
function getAlarmLevels()

When called, the RangeSliders are initialized (in initIonRangeSlider) and the AlarmLevels are updated for each slider.  This function is called as soons as the Icon for opening the Settings-Modal is clicked.

setAlarmLevels
function setAlarmLevels()

This function is used to save the chosen Alarm-Values in the Datamodel. It is called as soon as the "check" Button on the Settings-Modal is pressed.

Variables
knownAlarms
var knownAlarms

Saves the currently known Alarms.

alarmMuteDuration
var alarmMuteDuration

Stores the duration of the alarm mute time. Needs to be mutatable

alarmMuteInterval
var alarmMuteInterval

Stores the timer of the alarm mute during runtime.

Functions
toggleAlarmSound
function toggleAlarmSound()

Toggles the Alarm Sound. If alarms are active and sound is playing, the sound is muted.  If sounds are muted, button is clicked and alarms are active, the sound is unmuted.

createAlarmSound
function createAlarmSound(
alarmType,
state
)

In this function, the conditions to play an alarm sound are checked and potentially an alarm sound played.

Parameters
alarmType

Contains the type of the alarm.

state

Contains the current state of the alarm.

Variables
soundManagement
var soundManagement

Contains a reference to the initialized SoundManagement function. The function returns a state in a callback function. For descriptions, see SoundManagement

ecgMeasurement
var ecgMeasurement

Contains a reference to the initialized ECGMeasurement function. The function returns two callbacks. For descriptions, see ECGMeasurement

spo2Measurement
var spo2Measurement

Contains a reference to the initialized SpO2Measurement function. The function returns two callbacks. For descriptions, see SpO2Measurement

spo2Measurement

Contains a reference to the initialized SpO2Measurement function. The function returns a callback containing the measurered values. For descriptions, see SpO2Measurement

ecgGraph
var ecgGraph

Contains a reference to the initialized ECGGraph function. The callback invokes the next ecg calculation step.

spo2Graph
var spo2Graph

Contains a reference to the initialized Graph function. The callback invokes the next spo2 calculation step. See Graph for more information.

etco2Graph
var etco2Graph

Contains a reference to the initialized ETCO2Graph function. The callback invokes the next spo2 calculation step. See ETCO2Graph for more information.
